data.title: Template:Country data Cyprus
data.text:
Template:Country data Cyprus is an internal data container not intended to be transcluded directly. It is used indirectly by templates such as flag, flagicon, and others.

Standard parameters

Parameter nameValueMeaning alias Cyprus Main article name (Cyprus) flag alias Flag of Cyprus.svg Image name (File:Flag of Cyprus.svg, shown on right)

Flag variants

LabelFlag image (40px)Image name 1878Flag of the Turkish Republic of Northern Cyprus.svg1881Flag of Cyprus (1881–1922).svgcolonialBlue Ensign of Cyprus (1922).svgApril 1960Flag of Cyprus (1960).svg1960Flag of Cyprus (1960–2006).svg

Military ensigns

This nation's army ensign is the same as its national flag, so Template:Army produces the following:

{{army|Cyprus}} → Cypriot Ground Forces

Redirect aliases

This template can also be used via an alias name (implemented as a redirect to this template):

Alias name{{flag|alias}} output{{flagcountry|alias}} output CYP ( )Template:Country data CYPTemplate:Country data CYP

See What links here for a full list of redirects.

Example usage

{{flag|Cyprus}} → Cyprus

{{flagicon|Cyprus}} →

Using a flag variant

{{flag|Cyprus|1878}} → Cyprus

{{flagicon|Cyprus|1878}} →

Using a redirect alias

{{flagicon|CYP}} → Template:Country data CYP

{{flagcountry|CYP}} → Template:Country data CYP

{{flag|CYP}} → Template:Country data CYP
